<subpara id="RM000000SVT00ZX_07" type-id="51" category="05" proc-id="RM0250U___00002MN00000">
<name>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<atten4>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>DTCs P0327 and P0328 are for the bank 1 knock sensor circuit.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>DTCs P0332 and P0333 are for the bank 2 knock sensor circuit.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Read freeze frame data using the intelligent tester. The ECM records vehicle and driving condition information as freeze frame data the moment a DTC is stored. When troubleshooting, freeze frame data can be helpful in determining whether the vehicle was running or stopped, whether the engine was warmed up or not, whether the air-fuel ratio was lean or rich, as well as other data recorded at the time of a malfunction (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000PDS00ZX"/>).</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten4>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000SVT00ZX_08" type-id="01" category="01">
<name>PROCEDURE</name>
<testgrp id="RM000000SVT00ZX_08_0001" proc-id="RM0250U___00002MO00000">
<testtitle>READ OUTPUT DTC (CHECK KNOCK SENSOR CIRCUIT)</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Disconnect the CV1 connector.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="G041090E02" width="2.775699831in" height="3.779676365in"/>
</figure>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Using lead wires, connect the connectors as follows:</ptxt>
<table>
<tgroup cols="1" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="4.13in"/>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry>
<ptxt>Male Connector - Female Connector</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<ptxt>Terminal 2 - Terminal 4</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<ptxt>Terminal 1 - Terminal 3</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<ptxt>Terminal 4 - Terminal 2</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<ptxt>Terminal 3 - Terminal 1</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Warm up the engine.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Run the engine at 3,000 rpm for 10 seconds or more.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Connect the intelligent tester to the DLC3.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Turn the ignition switch on (IG) and turn the intelligent tester on.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Enter the following menus: DIAGNOSIS / ENHANCED OBD II / DTC INFO / CURRENT CODES.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Read the DTCs.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Result</title>
<table>
<tgroup cols="2" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="2.89in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="1.24in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Display</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>DTCs same as when vehicle brought in P0327, P0328 → P0327, P0328 or P0332, P0333 → P0332, P0333</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>A</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>DTCs different from when vehicle brought in P0327, P0328 → P0332, P0333 or P0332, P0333 → P0327, P0328</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>B</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Reconnect the CV1 connector.</ptxt>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000SVT00ZX_08_0002" fin="false">A</down>
<right ref="RM000000SVT00ZX_08_0007" fin="false">B</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
